The South African Property Owners Association (Sapoa) supports the new mediation process set out in the Protection of Investment Act draft regulations. The association states that it represents the economically significant property-owning sector of the economy and that good relations with foreign investors is important to its members. &ldquo;The recently announced mediation process in the Protection of Investment Act draft regulations is, therefore, a welcome proposal,&rdquo; it said. It also urged all parties to adopt a constructive attitude to encouraging foreign investment and good relations with investors generally.